\begin_layout Standard
This document describes the procedure to change a target in the AJA sputtering
 machine.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Turn the pump to the main chamber OFF.
 Wait until it depressurizes and you can open the main chamber.
 This will take less time than the load lock, but still several minutes.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Locate the target you wish to change by opening and closing the appropriate
 shutter in the computer interface.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Remove the shutter assembly by removing the two long screws holding it in
 place.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
The shutter will dangle there.
 Move it out of the way and remove the cowl enveloping the target.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Remove the target by removing the four short screws holding it into place.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Dielectrics will usually have a copper base.
 Metal targets are usually just the metal and must have a copper mesh electrical
ly coupling them to the base.
 Take care that you do not damage or lose this coupling.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Replace the target, cowl, and shutter by reversing the procedure.
 The removed target is to be sealed in a bag to protect it from dust.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Switch on the vacuum and wait about fifteen minutes for it to pump down.
\end_layout

